      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(control-ui): recognize namespaced reasoning tags in thinking extraction",
        "body": "## Problem\n`extractThinking()` in the Control UI only recognized bare legacy text-block tags such as `<think>` / `<thinking>`. Other parts of the UI already strip/suppress the broader reasoning-tag family, including namespaced MiniMax-style tags such as `<mm:thinking>`.\n\nWhen a model emits a namespaced reasoning block, the Control UI fallback path can leave the reasoning text in the visible answer instead of extracting it into the thinking section.\n\n## Fix\nExtend the legacy text-block extraction pattern to recognize namespaced reasoning tags while preserving the existing bare-tag behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: a message containing namespaced reasoning tags is now split into thinking content and visible answer content instead of leaking the reasoning block into the assistant response.\n\n**Focused verification run on this branch**:\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/message-extract.test.ts` -> 1 file / 8 tests passed\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxlint ui/src/ui/chat/message-extract.ts ui/src/ui/chat/message-extract.test.ts` -> clean\n\nThe focused test covers the changed `extractThinking()` behavior directly, including the namespaced tag case and existing extraction behavior.\n\n## Scope\nSmall Control UI parser-only change. No runtime API, storage, or protocol changes.\n",
